      "message": "[🟡 Suggestion] Line 56: Call push classification for starting PushForegroundService uses a case-sensitive substring check, while the later DHT proxy classifier correctly normalizes and matches exact comma-separated values. This inconsistency means a producer-side casing change such as `AudioCall` still restores/reconnects accounts via `isDhtProxyCallWakeup`, but does not start the foreground service/wakelock protection path intended for incoming calls. Reuse the normalized helper for both decisions.\n```suggestion\nval isCallNotification \u003d isDhtProxyCallWakeup(remoteMessage)\n        \u0026\u0026 remoteMessage.priority \u003d\u003d RemoteMessage.PRIORITY_HIGH\n```",
